CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 13, 1966, pg. 11B, reads: "PANCA WINNERS IN NAACP MEMBERS DRIVE - Among the workers winning PANCA Awards in NAACP's 1966 membership drive were left to right, Seated: Arie Lee Kyser, Jimetta Andrews, Sarah McCormick, Edna Jones, Coretta Ogburn, membership chairman, Carolyn Tate, Josephine Martin and Estelle Harrell. Standing: Florence B. Jones, Rev. B. S. Mason, Ruby Miller, Atty. Byrd R. Brown, president, Joliver Williams, George Smith Jr., Lisberger Blanks, James K. Anderson, Dolores Stanton, Nolene Powell, Pauline Hall, Cato Wimbish and Frances Lane. Missing from the photo are A. Laverne Mills, Gladys Coffey, James McCoy Jr., Theodore Jones, Willie Mae Lindsay, Francis E. McNairy, Vera Davis, pg. McMillan, Parker L. Hughes, Clipson Allen and Matthew Moore. - Harris Photo."
